"Involuntary Weight Loss"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_gm_s81_1",
"title":{
"__html":"Diagnosis"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"523223",
"children":[
"Diagnosis"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"ff4af5",
"children":[
"Causes of involuntary weight loss vary according to age (malignancy is most common in the young) and venue (depression, medications, dehydration, and issues related to dementia are most common in extended care facilities)."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"7f8fce",
"children":[
"Weight loss is commonly associated with depression and dementia. Socioeconomic and functional problems, such as difficulty obtaining food, lack of financial resources, and social isolation, cause or exacerbate weight loss. ",
{
"type":"alert",
"children":[
"Initial diagnostic testing is limited to basic studies (such as ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"thyroid-stimulating hormone",
"children":[
"TSH"
]
},
" level, HIV testing, age-appropriate cancer screening) unless the history and physical examination suggest a specific cause."
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"heading",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
"Don't Be Tricked"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"c4cc68",
"children":[
"Imaging of the thorax and abdomen with CT or MRI in the absence of supporting history, physical examination, or laboratory findings is not helpful."
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_gm_s81_2",
"title":{
"__html":"Treatment"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"4c4ac0",
"children":[
"Treatment"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"0cab7c",
"children":[
"Treat the specific underlying disorder. The proven benefit of oral nutritional supplementation for weight loss is limited. Appetite stimulants have been shown to promote weight gain, but a survival benefit has never been demonstrated."
]
},
